    <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-forest-ghost mb-5">
      Claremont, CA &nbsp;·&nbsp; Youth Sports Equity
    </p>

    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-semibold leading-tight max-w-3xl mb-6">
      Same city. Same taxes.<br>
      <em class="not-italic text-softball">Very different fields.</em>
    </h1>

    <p class="text-forest-ghost text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-10">
      Boys baseball plays on 3 fields at College Park. All are fenced and lockable, and 2 have lights.
      Girls softball has 3 fields too, split between La Puerta and Wheeler Parks.
      La Puerta has 2, both unlit and only one fenced. Wheeler has 1, lit but unfenced.
      Not one has both a fence and lights. Not one can be locked.
      California law calls that discrimination.
      We're asking the City Council to fix it.
    </p>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
